cs.CG, cs.GR, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.MM

The paper discusses a new algorithm for polyhedral meshing, which is a topic related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and graphics (cs.GR). The algorithm also involves the use of Voronoi-Delaunay meshes, which are commonly used in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper includes comparisons with state-of-the-art meshing methods, which could be considered a form of performance evaluation or benchmarking in multimedia (cs.MM).
